article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 45, SE Louisiana 38
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Matt Kingsley scored 21 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 45-38 victory over Southeastern Louisiana on Saturday night. Nick Shaw was the leading rebounder for the Lumberjacks (17-7, 9-3 Southland) and for the game with 19 rebounds while Kingsley's double-double was the eleventh of his career. Both teams had a poor shooting night. Southeastern Louisiana (9-16, 3-9) shot just 28 percent from the field in the game while the Lumberjacks made 38 percent of their field goals. Warrell Span and Brandon Fortenberry were the leading scorers for Southeastern Louisiana with 11 points each.
